// SMT Divergence + Volume Profile + Anchored VWAP + Iceberg [v2.1]
// Smart Money Technique (multi-symbol divergence) + session Volume Profile
// with previous-session levels, naked POC tracking, confluence alerts, status
// dashboard, session-anchored VWAP with σ bands, and iceberg/absorption
// detection.
//
// v1.0 — SMT divergence (multi-symbol, confirmed-pivot based).
// v1.1 — Volume Profile with developing POC/VAH/VAL + histogram; Pine v6
//        syntax fixes; div tooltip with values; pivot-marker toggle.
// v1.2 — Previous-session fixed POC/VAH/VAL lines; naked POC tracking with
//        auto-removal on touch; confluence-aware SMT alerts; status table
//        dashboard.
// v1.3 — Session-anchored VWAP + σ bands (1σ/2σ/3σ, optional fill); live
//        realtime projection (current-bar tick data added on top of confirmed
//        accumulation); plot-break at session start; AVWAP/σ levels added to
//        confluence detection and the dashboard.
// v1.4 — Iceberg / absorption detection (volume × range × close-position
//        proxy for hidden iceberg-order footprints); optional confluence
//        gating against VP and AVWAP levels; bull/bear bias from close
//        position; rich tooltip with vol/range/close stats; dashboard rows
//        for session count and last event.
// v1.5 — Verified bug-fix release:
//        • Naked-POC grace period now actually works. The 1-bar grace check
//          was previously comparing `bar_index` against `prevSessStartBar`
//          (the start bar of the prior session, far in the past), so the
//          condition was effectively always true and a new session's
//          first-bar straddle could immediately invalidate a just-created
//          nPOC. Now stores `bar_index` (creation bar) in a dedicated
//          `nakedPOCCreationBars` array.
//        • SMT alert + dashboard dedup per pivot bar. Previously, a pivot
//          that diverged against all three comparison symbols fired three
//          separate alerts and the dashboard would only show whichever
//          symbol happened to be evaluated last (sym3), losing context for
//          the other two. Now collects all diverging symbols on the pivot,
//          fires ONE combined alert ("Bearish SMT vs ES1!, NQ1!, YM1! | ..."),
//          and updates dashboard state once.
//        • VP histogram redraw gated to once-per-bar-change-or-close instead
//          of every realtime tick. Bins only update on `barstate.isconfirmed`,
//          so the previous every-tick delete-and-rebuild of ~24 boxes
//          produced identical output. Tracked via `lastVpDrawBar` var.
// v2.1 — Review follow-up. Performance fix for v2.0's bin recompute, plus
//        three real-but-narrow correctness fixes flagged by code review:
//        • CRITICAL — VP bin recompute is now incremental when the session
//          range is stable. v2.0 did a full `recomputeBinsFromRaw` on EVERY
//          confirmed bar, which is correct but O(N²·R) cumulatively across
//          a session. On extreme combos (Weekly+ anchor on M1 chart with
//          vpRows=80) late-session recomputes exceeded Pine's per-bar loop
//          budget (~200k iterations) and the indicator would crash.
//          Now: track `lastRecompHigh / lastRecompLow`. Full recompute only
//          when the session range actually expands (rare after the first
//          few bars); otherwise `accumulateCurrentBar` adds the current bar
//          incrementally in O(vpRows). Typical case is now O(N·R), same as
//          a naive incremental approach, while remaining drift-free.
//        • `levelsInBar` now checks the σ3 bands (only σ1/σ2 before). v1.9's
//          σ3 toggle was respected in `checkConfluence` but missed in
//          `levelsInBar`, so an iceberg sitting at ±3σ would not get the
//          confluence tag even though an SMT pivot at the same price would.
//        • Iceberg bull/bear classification is mutually exclusive at the
//          threshold = 0.5 edge case. Previously a doji bar (close exactly
//          at midpoint) would satisfy both `closeHigh` and `closeLow`, and
//          the code silently picked Bull. Now neither fires — a midpoint
//          close is genuinely ambiguous (no absorption side).
//        • `InVA` confluence tag no longer fires redundantly alongside
//          `pVAH` / `pVAL`. A price exactly at VAH used to produce both
//          tags; now `InVA` requires being strictly past both edges by more
//          than the tick tolerance.
// v2.0 — Correctness release. Three real bugs and two signal-quality gaps:
//        • SMT inverse-correlation SAMPLING fix. For Positive-correlated
//          comparison symbols we sample cmp.HIGH at chart pivot highs and
//          cmp.LOW at chart pivot lows — which captures cmp's matching pivot
//          value. For Inverse pairs (e.g., DXY vs EURUSD) the cmp pivots in
//          the OPPOSITE direction; the previous code still sampled the same
//          side as the chart pivot, so the divergence comparison was reading
//          off the wrong side of the cmp's bar. Now flips: inverse symbols
//          sample cmp.LOW at chart pivot HIGH and cmp.HIGH at chart pivot
//          LOW. Bull/Bear semantics unchanged; only the underlying sampled
//          values change, producing cleaner ICT-aligned divergence detection
//          on inverse pairs.
//        • VP bin drift eliminated. Bins were previously accumulated
//          incrementally as vpSessHigh/Low expanded — so volume deposited
//          early in the session (under a narrower range) referred to
//          different price levels than bins deposited later. POC and value
//          area drifted with the range. Replaced incremental accumulation
//          with `recomputeBinsFromRaw` (called on each confirmed bar and at
//          session finalization) — rebuilds bins from raw bar history using
//          the FINAL range. O(barsInSession × vpRows) per call but well
//          within Pine's compute budget; max_bars_back raised to 5000 to
//          cover long sessions.
//        • Naked-POC grace period off-by-one. The check was `> created + 1`
//          which is a 2-bar grace, but the documented intent was 1-bar.
//          Fixed to `> created` (skip only the creation bar itself).
//        • AVWAP confluence on session-boundary pivots was triggering
//          spuriously. On the first bar of a new session, AVWAP = hlc3 and
//          σ = 0 (single-bar VWAP), so any nearby price would falsely
//          "match" AVWAP. Added `pivSigma > 0` guard to both `checkConfluence`
//          and `levelsInBar` — skips AVWAP/σ confluence when the AVWAP
//          hasn't yet developed.
//        • Iceberg confluence now checks the developing-session POC/VAH/VAL
//          (`currDevPOC/VAH/VAL`) in addition to the previous-session
//          levels, naked POCs, and AVWAP/σ. An iceberg sitting at the
//          developing POC is a high-quality signal that was previously
//          silent in the confluence tag.
// v1.9 — Audit bug-fix release:
//        • Iceberg detection no longer self-dilutes its own threshold. The
//          volume SMA and ATR are now computed with a [1]-offset (trailing
//          20 / 14 bars EXCLUDING the current bar). Previously a 2× volume
//          spike raised its own SMA enough that the realised ratio came in
//          just under iceVolMult, causing real iceberg bars to be missed.
//          Same fix applied to ATR for consistency. Volume-ratio displayed
//          in the iceberg tooltip is now accurate too.
//        • HVN/LVN lines no longer extend right across session boundaries.
//          They are session-bound markers — extending them right (alongside
//          POC/VAH/VAL, the genuine forward-reference levels) was visually
//          polluting subsequent sessions. Now always extend.none.
//        • HVN/LVN lines and per-bin volume labels are DELETED on session
//          reset, not orphaned. Histogram boxes are still orphaned (they
//          anchor to the past session's right edge and serve as a historical
//          profile reference); HVN/LVN lines and per-bin labels would either
//          clutter the new session or eat into Pine's 500-label budget over
//          many sessions.
//        • Confluence strings are now right-trimmed (no trailing space).
//        • Sentiment histogram bins in Twin layout no longer round up to a
//          minimum 1-bar width — near-balanced bins are now visually quiet
//          instead of falsely displaying a thin neutral bar.
// v1.8 — Inverse correlation support for SMT divergence:
//        Previously the SMT logic implicitly assumed all comparison symbols
//        were POSITIVELY correlated with the chart (move together). For
//        inverse pairs (EURUSD vs DXY, SPY vs VIX, BTC vs gold, etc.) the
//        divergence condition is actually the OPPOSITE — they're expected to
//        move in opposite directions, so a divergence is when they move the
//        SAME direction.
//        • Per-symbol Positive/Inverse correlation dropdown added to each
//          comparison row. Each symbol can be configured independently.
//        • Divergence check now flips based on correlation: positive pairs
//          fire on opposite movement, inverse pairs fire on matching
//          movement, exactly as ICT defines SMT divergence on inverse pairs.
//        • Diverged-symbol list (used in alerts + dashboard) tags inverse
//          pairs with " (inv)" suffix so you can see at a glance which
//          correlation type triggered the signal.
// v1.7 — VP Visualization upgrade (LuxAlgo-style, signature pieces only):
//        • Twin Profile layout: optional side-by-side rendering — sentiment
//          histogram (BBP per bin, green/red) on the left and volume
//          histogram on the right. Each shares the same vertical price
//          range, anchored at the right edge of the latest bar. Single-mode
//          layout (overlay sentiment color on volume bins) remains default.
//        • Per-bin volume labels (optional). Each bin gets a small label
//          showing `{vol} ({%-of-session})` for analytical depth.
//        • Profile edge labels (optional, on by default). Profile High and
//          Profile Low labels at the session range extremes, with tooltips
//          carrying total volume, bar count, and range %.
//        • Tracked drawings expanded to include `vpSentBoxes`, `vpBinLabels`,
//          `vpHighLabel`, `vpLowLabel` — all cleaned up on session reset
//          and re-created on each redraw cycle.
//        • Deliberate skips (per analyst's recommendation): no heatmap, no
//          developing-POC polyline, no three-tier color gradient, no
//          fixed-range anchor mode, no LuxAlgo sentiment-zone marker.
// v1.6 — Sentiment Profile + Money Flow + HVN/LVN (LuxAlgo-inspired):
//        • Per-bin bull/bear split (Sentiment Profile). A parallel
//          `vpBinsBull` array tracks the bull-classified volume per bin;
//          bear = total − bull. Bins colored by net sign when enabled —
//          green for buyer-dominated, red for seller-dominated, neutral
//          otherwise. Two classification methods: bar polarity (close vs
//          open) or buying pressure (close position in bar range).
//        • Money Flow weighting toggle. When ON, bin weight is
//          `volume × overlap × bin-midprice` (dollar value transacted) vs
//          the default `volume × overlap` (share count). More meaningful
//          on instruments with wide price variation.
//        • HVN / LVN classification. High Volume Nodes (≥ threshold % of
//          POC) and Low Volume Nodes (≤ threshold %) drawn as horizontal
//          lines through the current session, identifying value zones and
//          thin "no-mans-land" pass-through levels respectively.
//        • Prev-session POC sentiment captured at finalization and surfaced
//          in confluence tags as `pPOC(Bull)` / `pPOC(Bear)` so a bearish
//          iceberg at a buyer-dominated prior POC reads as a sharper
//          divergence signal than one at a neutral level.
//        • Dashboard: session sentiment summary (Bull% / Bear%), HVN/LVN
//          counts, prev-POC dashboard cell tagged with sentiment.
//
// NOTE on icebergs: true iceberg detection needs Level 2 / order-book data,
// which Pine does not have. This implementation uses the standard candlestick
// proxy: high volume + narrow range + extreme close = absorption footprint.
// Best paired with VP/AVWAP confluence gating for high-quality signals.

//@version=6
indicator('SMT + VP + AVWAP + Ice [v2.1]', 'SMT+VP v2.1', overlay = true, max_lines_count = 500, max_labels_count = 500, max_boxes_count = 500, max_bars_back = 5000)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Constants
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GREEN = #089981
RED   = #F23645
GRAY  = #878b94
GOLD  = #FFC107
BLUE  = #2196F3
AMBER = #FF9800

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Inputs — SMT
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
grpPivot = 'SMT — Pivot Detection'
pivotLen     = input.int(5, 'Pivot Length', minval = 1, maxval = 50, tooltip = 'Bars on each side required to confirm a swing pivot.', group = grpPivot)
pivotSrcMode = input.string('Wick', 'Pivot Source', options = ['Wick', 'Body'], tooltip = 'Wick uses high/low; Body uses max/min of open/close.', group = grpPivot)
showPivotMarkers = input.bool(false, 'Show Pivot Markers', group = grpPivot)

grpSymbols = 'SMT — Comparison Symbols'
// Each symbol row: [enable checkbox] [symbol picker] [Positive/Inverse correlation].
// Positive: chart and comparison are expected to move TOGETHER (ES/NQ/YM, BTC/ETH).
// Inverse:  chart and comparison are expected to move OPPOSITE (EURUSD/DXY, SPY/VIX).
// Divergence logic flips automatically based on this setting.
sym1Enabled = input.bool(true,  '', inline = 's1', group = grpSymbols)
sym1        = input.symbol('CME_MINI:ES1!', 'Symbol 1', inline = 's1', group = grpSymbols)
sym1Corr    = input.string('Positive', '', options = ['Positive', 'Inverse'], inline = 's1', group = grpSymbols, tooltip = 'Positive: chart and symbol move together (ES vs NQ, BTC vs ETH). Inverse: chart and symbol move opposite (EURUSD vs DXY, SPY vs VIX). The divergence condition flips automatically for Inverse.')
sym2Enabled = input.bool(true,  '', inline = 's2', group = grpSymbols)
sym2        = input.symbol('CME_MINI:NQ1!', 'Symbol 2', inline = 's2', group = grpSymbols)
sym2Corr    = input.string('Positive', '', options = ['Positive', 'Inverse'], inline = 's2', group = grpSymbols)
sym3Enabled = input.bool(false, '', inline = 's3', group = grpSymbols)
sym3        = input.symbol('CBOT_MINI:YM1!', 'Symbol 3', inline = 's3', group = grpSymbols)
sym3Corr    = input.string('Positive', '', options = ['Positive', 'Inverse'], inline = 's3', group = grpSymbols)

grpStyle = 'SMT — Style'
bullColor   = input.color(GREEN, 'Bullish SMT', group = grpStyle)
bearColor   = input.color(RED,   'Bearish SMT', group = grpStyle)
lineWidth   = input.int(2, 'Line Width', minval = 1, maxval = 5, group = grpStyle)
lineStyleIn = input.string('Dashed', 'Line Style', options = ['Solid', 'Dashed', 'Dotted'], group = grpStyle)
showLabel   = input.bool(true, 'Show Symbol Label', group = grpStyle)
labelSize   = input.string('small', 'Label Size', options = ['tiny', 'small', 'normal'], group = grpStyle)

grpAlerts = 'SMT — Alerts'
alertBull = input.bool(true, 'Alert on Bullish SMT', group = grpAlerts)
alertBear = input.bool(true, 'Alert on Bearish SMT', group = grpAlerts)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Inputs — Volume Profile (Current + Previous Session)
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
grpVP = 'Volume Profile'
vpEnabled    = input.bool(true, 'Show Volume Profile', group = grpVP)
vpAnchorIn   = input.string('Daily', 'Anchor', options = ['Daily', 'Weekly', 'Monthly'], group = grpVP)
vpRows       = input.int(24, 'Profile Rows', minval = 5, maxval = 80, tooltip = 'More rows = finer resolution but more boxes.', group = grpVP)
vpValueAreaP = input.float(70.0, 'Value Area %', minval = 50, maxval = 95, step = 1, group = grpVP) / 100.0
vpShowHist   = input.bool(true, 'Show Histogram', group = grpVP)
vpHistWidth  = input.int(40, 'Histogram Width (bars)', minval = 5, maxval = 200, group = grpVP)
vpShowPOC    = input.bool(true, 'Show Current POC',    group = grpVP)
vpShowVA     = input.bool(true, 'Show Current VAH/VAL', group = grpVP)
vpShowLabels = input.bool(true, 'Show Price Labels', group = grpVP)
vpExtend     = input.bool(true, 'Extend Current Levels Right', group = grpVP)
vpPocColor   = input.color(GOLD, 'POC Color', group = grpVP)
vpVaColor    = input.color(BLUE, 'VAH/VAL Color', group = grpVP)
vpVaFill     = input.color(color.new(BLUE, 80), 'Value Area Fill', group = grpVP)
vpOutFill    = input.color(color.new(GRAY, 80), 'Outside VA Fill', group = grpVP)

grpPrev = 'Previous Session Levels'
vpShowPrev      = input.bool(true, 'Show Previous Session POC/VAH/VAL', group = grpPrev)
vpPrevPocColor  = input.color(color.new(GOLD, 20), 'Prev POC Color', group = grpPrev)
vpPrevVaColor   = input.color(color.new(BLUE, 20), 'Prev VAH/VAL Color', group = grpPrev)
vpPrevLineWidth = input.int(2, 'Prev POC Line Width', minval = 1, maxval = 4, group = grpPrev)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Inputs — Volume Profile Advanced (Money Flow, Sentiment, HVN/LVN)
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
grpVPAdv = 'VP Advanced — Sentiment & Money Flow'
vpSource          = input.string('Volume', 'Profile Source', options = ['Volume', 'Money Flow'], tooltip = 'Volume: bin = overlap × volume (share/contract count). Money Flow: bin = overlap × volume × bin-midprice (dollar value transacted). Money Flow gives a more meaningful picture on instruments with wide price variation (crypto, equities); for tight-range forex pairs the difference is small.', group = grpVPAdv)
vpSentiment       = input.bool(true, 'Color Bins by Sentiment (Bull/Bear)', tooltip = 'Splits each bin into bull vs bear volume; bin is colored green if buyers dominated at that price level, red if sellers did, gray if balanced. When OFF, bins use the standard inside-VA / outside-VA colors.', group = grpVPAdv)
vpSentimentMethod = input.string('Bar Polarity', 'Sentiment Method', options = ['Bar Polarity', 'Buying Pressure'], tooltip = 'Bar Polarity: bullish if close > open. Buying Pressure: bullish if (close-low) > (high-close), i.e. closed in upper half of bar range.', group = grpVPAdv)
vpBullBinColor    = input.color(color.new(GREEN, 60), 'Bullish Bin Color', group = grpVPAdv)
vpBearBinColor    = input.color(color.new(RED, 60), 'Bearish Bin Color', group = grpVPAdv)
vpNeutralBinColor = input.color(color.new(GRAY, 70), 'Neutral Bin Color', group = grpVPAdv)

grpHVN = 'HVN / LVN Classification'
vpShowHVN      = input.bool(false, 'Mark HVN / LVN Levels', tooltip = 'High Volume Nodes (HVN) = consolidation/value zones — price tends to dwell. Low Volume Nodes (LVN) = thin zones — price tends to traverse quickly, good no-mans-land for stop placement.', group = grpHVN)
vpHVNThreshold = input.float(0.7, 'HVN Threshold (% of POC)', minval = 0.3, maxval = 0.95, step = 0.05, tooltip = 'Bin counts as HVN if its volume is at least this fraction of the POC bin. 0.7 = 70%.', group = grpHVN)
vpLVNThreshold = input.float(0.2, 'LVN Threshold (% of POC)', minval = 0.05, maxval = 0.4, step = 0.05, tooltip = 'Bin counts as LVN if its volume is between 0 and this fraction of the POC bin. 0.2 = 20%.', group = grpHVN)
vpHVNColor     = input.color(color.new(GOLD, 50), 'HVN Line Color', group = grpHVN)
vpLVNColor     = input.color(color.new(GRAY, 60), 'LVN Line Color', group = grpHVN)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Inputs — VP Visualization (Twin Layout, Bin Labels, Edge Labels)
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
grpVPViz = 'VP Visualization'
vpProfileLayout  = input.string('Single', 'Profile Layout', options = ['Single', 'Twin (Volume + Sentiment)'], tooltip = 'Single: one histogram with bins colored by sentiment or VA. Twin: separate sentiment histogram (closer to chart, width proportional to |Bull-Bear| per bin) and volume histogram (further right, width proportional to total volume).', group = grpVPViz)
vpShowBinLabels  = input.bool(false, 'Show Per-Bin Volume Labels', tooltip = 'Each histogram bin gets a small label showing its volume amount and % of session total. Adds visual density — use selectively.', group = grpVPViz)
vpShowEdgeLabels = input.bool(true, 'Show Profile High / Low Labels', tooltip = 'Mark the top and bottom of the session profile range with labels. Hover for total volume, bar count, range %.', group = grpVPViz)
vpTwinSentBull   = input.color(color.new(GREEN, 55), 'Twin: Bull Sentiment Color', group = grpVPViz)
vpTwinSentBear   = input.color(color.new(RED, 55),   'Twin: Bear Sentiment Color', group = grpVPViz)
vpTwinVolColor   = input.color(color.new(BLUE, 70),  'Twin: Volume Color', tooltip = 'In Twin layout the volume bins are color-neutral by default since sentiment is already shown on the other histogram.', group = grpVPViz)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Inputs — Naked POCs
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
grpNPOC = 'Naked POCs'
nPocEnabled = input.bool(true, 'Track Naked POCs', tooltip = 'Save each completed session POC; remove when price re-touches.', group = grpNPOC)
nPocMax     = input.int(20, 'Max Tracked', minval = 1, maxval = 100, group = grpNPOC)
nPocColor   = input.color(color.new(AMBER, 30), 'Color', group = grpNPOC)
nPocStyleIn = input.string('Dotted', 'Line Style', options = ['Solid', 'Dashed', 'Dotted'], group = grpNPOC)
nPocLabels  = input.bool(true, 'Show Labels', group = grpNPOC)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Inputs — Anchored VWAP + σ Bands
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
grpAvwap = 'Anchored VWAP'
avwapEnabled = input.bool(true, 'Show Anchored VWAP', tooltip = 'Session-anchored VWAP using the same anchor as Volume Profile.', group = grpAvwap)
avwapColor   = input.color(#FF6D00, 'AVWAP Color', group = grpAvwap)
avwapWidth   = input.int(2, 'AVWAP Line Width', minval = 1, maxval = 4, group = grpAvwap)

showSigma1  = input.bool(true,  '', inline = 'sg1', group = grpAvwap)
sigma1Mult  = input.float(1.0, '±σ #1 ×', minval = 0.1, maxval = 5, step = 0.1, inline = 'sg1', group = grpAvwap)
sigma1Color = input.color(color.new(#FF6D00, 40), '', inline = 'sg1', group = grpAvwap)

showSigma2  = input.bool(true,  '', inline = 'sg2', group = grpAvwap)
sigma2Mult  = input.float(2.0, '±σ #2 ×', minval = 0.1, maxval = 5, step = 0.1, inline = 'sg2', group = grpAvwap)
sigma2Color = input.color(color.new(#FF6D00, 60), '', inline = 'sg2', group = grpAvwap)

showSigma3  = input.bool(false, '', inline = 'sg3', group = grpAvwap)
sigma3Mult  = input.float(3.0, '±σ #3 ×', minval = 0.1, maxval = 5, step = 0.1, inline = 'sg3', group = grpAvwap)
sigma3Color = input.color(color.new(#FF6D00, 75), '', inline = 'sg3', group = grpAvwap)

fillBands    = input.bool(true, 'Fill Between Bands', group = grpAvwap)
fillOpacity  = input.int(92, 'Fill Opacity (lower = darker)', minval = 60, maxval = 99, group = grpAvwap)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Inputs — Confluence
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
grpConf = 'Confluence'
confEnabled = input.bool(true, 'Detect Confluence at SMT', group = grpConf)
confTicks   = input.int(10, 'Distance (ticks)', minval = 1, maxval = 200, tooltip = 'SMT pivots within this many ticks of a VP/AVWAP level count as confluence.', group = grpConf)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Inputs — Iceberg / Absorption
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
grpIce = 'Iceberg / Absorption'
iceEnabled        = input.bool(true, 'Detect Iceberg / Absorption', tooltip = 'Flags high-volume narrow-range bars that close at one extreme — a proxy for hidden iceberg-order absorption.', group = grpIce)
iceVolMult        = input.float(2.0, 'Volume Multiplier (× SMA20)', minval = 1.0, maxval = 10, step = 0.1, tooltip = 'Bar volume must exceed this multiple of the 20-bar volume SMA.', group = grpIce)
iceRangeMult      = input.float(0.5, 'Max Range (× ATR14)', minval = 0.1, maxval = 2.0, step = 0.05, tooltip = 'Bar range must be LESS than this multiple of ATR(14). Narrow range = absorption.', group = grpIce)
iceCloseThreshold = input.float(0.33, 'Close Position Threshold', minval = 0.1, maxval = 0.5, step = 0.05, tooltip = 'Close must be in top/bottom N of bar range. 0.33 = top/bottom third.', group = grpIce)
iceRequireConf    = input.bool(true, 'Require VP/AVWAP Confluence', tooltip = 'Only fire icebergs whose bar range straddles a tracked level.', group = grpIce)
iceAlertEnabled   = input.bool(true, 'Alert on Iceberg', group = grpIce)
iceBullColor      = input.color(GREEN, 'Bullish Iceberg', group = grpIce)
iceBearColor      = input.color(RED,   'Bearish Iceberg', group = grpIce)
iceMarkerSize     = input.string('small', 'Marker Size', options = ['tiny', 'small', 'normal'], group = grpIce)
iceMarkerText     = input.string('🧊', 'Marker Text', tooltip = 'Falls back to text if emoji does not render on your platform.', group = grpIce)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Inputs — Dashboard
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
grpDash = 'Dashboard'
showDash = input.bool(true, 'Show Dashboard', group = grpDash)
dashPos  = input.string('Top Right', 'Position', options = ['Top Right', 'Top Left', 'Bottom Right', 'Bottom Left', 'Middle Right'], group = grpDash)
dashSize = input.string('small', 'Text Size', options = ['tiny', 'small', 'normal'], group = grpDash)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Helpers
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
getLineStyle(string s) =>
    switch s
        'Solid'  => line.style_solid
        'Dashed' => line.style_dashed
        'Dotted' => line.style_dotted
        =>          line.style_dashed

getLabelSize(string s) =>
    switch s
        'tiny'   => size.tiny
        'small'  => size.small
        'normal' => size.normal
        =>          size.small

getDashPosition(string s) =>
    switch s
        'Top Left'      => position.top_left
        'Top Right'     => position.top_right
        'Bottom Left'   => position.bottom_left
        'Bottom Right'  => position.bottom_right
        'Middle Right'  => position.middle_right
        =>                 position.top_right

shortName(string s) =>
    int colonIdx = str.pos(s, ':')
    na(colonIdx) ? s : str.substring(s, colonIdx + 1)

pivotSrcHigh = pivotSrcMode == 'Body' ? math.max(open, close) : high
pivotSrcLow  = pivotSrcMode == 'Body' ? math.min(open, close) : low

// Session boundary detection — used by both Volume Profile and Anchored VWAP.
vpAnchorTF = vpAnchorIn == 'Daily' ? 'D' : vpAnchorIn == 'Weekly' ? 'W' : 'M'
isNewVPSession = ta.change(time(vpAnchorTF)) != 0

// Profile computation — returns POC bin index, value-area bin indices, total volume.
computeProfile(array<float> bins, int rows, float vaTargetRatio) =>
    int   pocIdx = 0
    float maxV   = 0.0
    float totalV = 0.0
    for i = 0 to rows - 1
        float v = array.get(bins, i)
        totalV += v
        if v > maxV
            maxV   := v
            pocIdx := i
    int   vaL = pocIdx
    int   vaH = pocIdx
    float vaV = array.get(bins, pocIdx)
    float target = totalV * vaTargetRatio
    while vaV < target and (vaL > 0 or vaH < rows - 1)
        float upV = vaH < rows - 1 ? array.get(bins, vaH + 1) : -1.0
        float dnV = vaL > 0        ? array.get(bins, vaL - 1) : -1.0
        if upV < 0 and dnV < 0
            break
        if upV >= dnV
            vaH += 1
            vaV += upV
        else
            vaL -= 1
            vaV += dnV
    [pocIdx, vaL, vaH, totalV]


//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// COMPARISON SYMBOL DATA + PIVOTS (must run on every bar before SMT block)
//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
[s1High, s1Low] = request.security(sym1, timeframe.period, [pivotSrcHigh, pivotSrcLow], lookahead = barmerge.lookahead_off)
[s2High, s2Low] = request.security(sym2, timeframe.period, [pivotSrcHigh, pivotSrcLow], lookahead = barmerge.lookahead_off)
[s3High, s3Low] = request.security(sym3, timeframe.period, [pivotSrcHigh, pivotSrcLow], lookahead = barmerge.lookahead_off)

phVal = ta.pivothigh(pivotSrcHigh, pivotLen, pivotLen)
plVal = ta.pivotlow (pivotSrcLow,  pivotLen, pivotLen)

//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// ANCHORED VWAP + σ BANDS
//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Session-anchored VWAP. Confirmed-bar accumulation gives exact historical
// values; the realtime bar adds a live projection on top so the displayed
// VWAP is up-to-date instead of one bar stale.
//
// σ formula:  variance = Σ(P²·V)/ΣV − VWAP²    (O(1) per bar, no growing array)

var float cumPV   = 0.0   // Σ(typical price · volume)
var float cumV    = 0.0   // Σ(volume)
var float cumPV2  = 0.0   // Σ(typical² · volume)

// Confirmed-bar accumulation. On a session boundary, reset to this bar only.
// nz(volume) — some feeds (OANDA forex, certain index feeds) report `na`
// volume on individual bars. Without nz(), a single na bar poisons the whole
// cumulative sum via NaN propagation and AVWAP becomes na forever.
if avwapEnabled and barstate.isconfirmed
    float tp = hlc3
    float vol = nz(volume)
    float pv = tp * vol
    if isNewVPSession or cumV == 0
        cumPV  := pv
        cumV   := vol
        cumPV2 := tp * pv
    else
        cumPV  += pv
        cumV   += vol
        cumPV2 += tp * pv

// Live projection — for the realtime bar before close, add the running
// hlc3·volume on top of the confirmed accumulation so the AVWAP displayed
// includes the current tick.
float liveCumPV  = cumPV
float liveCumV   = cumV
float liveCumPV2 = cumPV2
if avwapEnabled and not barstate.isconfirmed
    float tp = hlc3
    float vol = nz(volume)
    float pv = tp * vol
    if isNewVPSession or cumV == 0
        liveCumPV  := pv
        liveCumV   := vol
        liveCumPV2 := tp * pv
    else
        liveCumPV  := cumPV  + pv
        liveCumV   := cumV   + vol
        liveCumPV2 := cumPV2 + tp * pv

float avwap      = avwapEnabled and liveCumV > 0 ? liveCumPV / liveCumV : na
float avwapVar   = avwapEnabled and liveCumV > 0 ? math.max(0.0, liveCumPV2 / liveCumV - avwap * avwap) : na
float avwapSigma = na(avwapVar) ? na : math.sqrt(avwapVar)

float avwapU1 = na(avwap) or na(avwapSigma) ? na : avwap + sigma1Mult * avwapSigma
float avwapL1 = na(avwap) or na(avwapSigma) ? na : avwap - sigma1Mult * avwapSigma
float avwapU2 = na(avwap) or na(avwapSigma) ? na : avwap + sigma2Mult * avwapSigma
float avwapL2 = na(avwap) or na(avwapSigma) ? na : avwap - sigma2Mult * avwapSigma
float avwapU3 = na(avwap) or na(avwapSigma) ? na : avwap + sigma3Mult * avwapSigma
float avwapL3 = na(avwap) or na(avwapSigma) ? na : avwap - sigma3Mult * avwapSigma

//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// STATE
//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// SMT state — previous-pivot snapshots, used to evaluate consecutive divergences.
var float prevPHChart = na
var float prevPHS1    = na
var float prevPHS2    = na
var float prevPHS3    = na
var int   prevPHBar   = na

var float prevPLChart = na
var float prevPLS1    = na
var float prevPLS2    = na
var float prevPLS3    = na
var int   prevPLBar   = na

// Last-fired SMT event for the dashboard.
var int    lastBullBar = na
var string lastBullSym = ''
var float  lastBullPrice = na
var bool   lastBullConf = false
var int    lastBearBar = na
var string lastBearSym = ''
var float  lastBearPrice = na
var bool   lastBearConf = false

// Iceberg tracking — session count + last event.
var int    iceCount    = 0
var int    lastIceBar  = na
var string lastIceType = ''   // 'Bull' or 'Bear'
var bool   lastIceConf = false

// VP session aggregates.
var float vpSessHigh  = na
var float vpSessLow   = na
var int   vpSessStart = na
var array<float> vpBins     = array.new<float>(vpRows, 0.0)   // total volume per bin
var array<float> vpBinsBull = array.new<float>(vpRows, 0.0)   // bull-classified volume per bin; bear = vpBins - vpBinsBull

// VP developing-session drawings.
var array<box>   vpBoxes     = array.new<box>()     // volume histogram bins
var array<box>   vpSentBoxes = array.new<box>()     // sentiment histogram bins (twin layout only)
var array<line>  vpHVNLines  = array.new<line>()    // HVN/LVN markers (developing-session only)
var array<label> vpBinLabels = array.new<label>()   // per-bin volume labels (toggle)
var line  vpPocLine   = na
var line  vpVahLine   = na
var line  vpValLine   = na
var label vpPocLabel  = na
var label vpVahLabel  = na
var label vpValLabel  = na
var label vpHighLabel = na   // profile high edge label
var label vpLowLabel  = na   // profile low edge label

// Cached current developing levels (for confluence + dashboard).
var float currDevPOC = na
var float currDevVAH = na
var float currDevVAL = na

// HVN/LVN counts (for dashboard).
var int hvnCount = 0
var int lvnCount = 0

// State for the incremental-vs-recompute decision. We only do a full
// `recomputeBinsFromRaw` when the session range has actually expanded since
// the last recompute. While the range is stable, each confirmed bar just
// adds its volume into the existing (already-correctly-aligned) bins. This
// turns the worst case from O(N²·R) per session down to O(N·R) for typical
// sessions where the range stabilizes after the first few bars.
var float lastRecompHigh = na
var float lastRecompLow  = na

// Per-session bar counter — used in the profile edge-label tooltip so the user
// can see how many bars are aggregated into the developing profile.
var int vpSessBarCount = 0

// Tracks the last bar on which the VP histogram was redrawn so we don't
// delete-and-rebuild ~24 boxes on every realtime tick when nothing changed.
var int lastVpDrawBar = na

// Previous session finalized levels.
var float  prevSessPOC = na
var float  prevSessVAH = na
var float  prevSessVAL = na
var int    prevSessStartBar = na
var int    prevSessEndBar   = na
var string prevSessPOCSentiment = na   // 'Bull' / 'Bear' / 'Neutral' — used to enrich confluence tags
var line   prevPocLine  = na
var line   prevVahLine  = na
var line   prevValLine  = na
var label  prevPocLabel = na
var label  prevVahLabel = na
var label  prevValLabel = na

// Naked POC tracking — each entry is a session-finalized POC that hasn't been
// re-touched yet. Parallel arrays for price, creation bar (= the bar where the
// POC was pushed, used for the 1-bar grace period in the touch check), line,
// and label.
var array<float> nakedPOCs            = array.new<float>()
var array<int>   nakedPOCCreationBars = array.new<int>()
var array<line>  nakedPOCLines        = array.new<line>()
var array<label> nakedPOCLabels       = array.new<label>()

// Dashboard table.
var table dashTable = na

// Style derivations.
lineStyle  = getLineStyle(lineStyleIn)
nPocStyle  = getLineStyle(nPocStyleIn)
lblSize    = getLabelSize(labelSize)
dashTxtSz  = getLabelSize(dashSize)

//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// HELPERS — drift-free VP recomputation
//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Recompute vpBins / vpBinsBull from raw bar history using the CURRENT
// vpSessHigh / vpSessLow as the bin range. Required because vpSessHigh/Low
// expand during the session — under incremental accumulation, bins assigned
// in early bars would refer to different price ranges than bins assigned
// later. Recomputing from raw on each redraw eliminates this drift.
//
// Must be defined AFTER the STATE section because it references the global
// `vpBins` / `vpBinsBull` arrays and the `vpSessHigh` / `vpSessLow` /
// `vpSessStart` / `vpRows` / `vpSource` / `vpSentimentMethod` symbols. Pine
// does not forward-resolve function-body identifiers.
//
// startOffset = 0 → include the current bar (developing redraw)
// startOffset = 1 → exclude the current bar (used at session finalization,
//                   where the current bar is the first bar of the NEW session
//                   and shouldn't be counted in the prior session's profile).
recomputeBinsFromRaw(int startOffset, int endOffset) =>
    array.fill(vpBins,     0.0)
    array.fill(vpBinsBull, 0.0)
    if endOffset >= startOffset and not na(vpSessHigh) and not na(vpSessLow) and vpSessHigh > vpSessLow
        float binSize  = (vpSessHigh - vpSessLow) / vpRows
        bool  moneyFlow = vpSource == 'Money Flow'
        if binSize > 0
            for offset = startOffset to endOffset
                float bH = high[offset]
                float bL = low[offset]
                float bC = close[offset]
                float bO = open[offset]
                float bV = nz(volume[offset])
                float bRange = bH - bL
                if bRange > 0 and bV > 0
                    bool barBull = vpSentimentMethod == 'Bar Polarity' ? bC > bO : (bC - bL) > (bH - bC)
                    for i = 0 to vpRows - 1
                        float binLow  = vpSessLow + i * binSize
                        float binHigh = binLow + binSize
                        float overlap = math.max(0.0, math.min(bH, binHigh) - math.max(bL, binLow))
                        if overlap > 0
                            float ratio       = overlap / bRange
                            float binMidPrice = binLow + binSize * 0.5
                            float weight      = moneyFlow ? bV * ratio * binMidPrice : bV * ratio
                            array.set(vpBins, i, array.get(vpBins, i) + weight)
                            if barBull
                                array.set(vpBinsBull, i, array.get(vpBinsBull, i) + weight)
    0

// Incremental: add ONLY the current bar's volume into the existing bin array
// using the current session range. Safe to call when the range is unchanged
// from the last full recompute — bin boundaries are stable, so adding to
// existing indices is correct. O(vpRows) per call.
accumulateCurrentBar() =>
    if not na(vpSessHigh) and not na(vpSessLow) and vpSessHigh > vpSessLow
        float binSize  = (vpSessHigh - vpSessLow) / vpRows
        float barRange = high - low
        float vol      = nz(volume)
        if barRange > 0 and binSize > 0 and vol > 0
            bool barBull   = vpSentimentMethod == 'Bar Polarity' ? close > open : (close - low) > (high - close)
            bool moneyFlow = vpSource == 'Money Flow'
            for i = 0 to vpRows - 1
                float binLow  = vpSessLow + i * binSize
                float binHigh = binLow + binSize
                float overlap = math.max(0.0, math.min(high, binHigh) - math.max(low, binLow))
                if overlap > 0
                    float ratio       = overlap / barRange
                    float binMidPrice = binLow + binSize * 0.5
                    float weight      = moneyFlow ? vol * ratio * binMidPrice : vol * ratio
                    array.set(vpBins, i, array.get(vpBins, i) + weight)
                    if barBull
                        array.set(vpBinsBull, i, array.get(vpBinsBull, i) + weight)
    0

//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// HELPERS — confluence
//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Returns a confluence description string, empty if none. Checks the pivot
// price against previous-session levels, active naked POCs, and the AVWAP/σ
// bands at the pivot bar (offset back by `barOffset`).
checkConfluence(float price, float tickDist, int barOffset) =>
    string out = ''
    if not confEnabled or na(price)
        out
    else
        float td = tickDist * syminfo.mintick
        bool atVAH = not na(prevSessVAH) and math.abs(price - prevSessVAH) <= td
        bool atVAL = not na(prevSessVAL) and math.abs(price - prevSessVAL) <= td
        if not na(prevSessPOC) and math.abs(price - prevSessPOC) <= td
            string sentSuffix = na(prevSessPOCSentiment) or prevSessPOCSentiment == 'Neutral' ? '' : '(' + prevSessPOCSentiment + ')'
            out := out + 'pPOC' + sentSuffix + ' '
        if atVAH
            out := out + 'pVAH '
        if atVAL
            out := out + 'pVAL '
        // InVA fires only when CLEARLY inside the value area (strictly past
        // both edges by more than the tick tolerance). Prevents redundant
        // "pVAH InVA" tag pairs on boundary-hugging prices.
        if not atVAH and not atVAL and not na(prevSessVAH) and not na(prevSessVAL) and price > prevSessVAL + td and price < prevSessVAH - td
            out := out + 'InVA '
        int sz = array.size(nakedPOCs)
        if sz > 0
            for i = 0 to sz - 1
                float p = array.get(nakedPOCs, i)
                if math.abs(price - p) <= td
                    out := out + 'nPOC@' + str.tostring(p, format.mintick) + ' '
                    break
        // AVWAP + σ bands at the pivot bar. Require pivSigma > 0 to avoid
        // false-positive confluence on session-boundary bars, where the
        // AVWAP has only 1 bar of accumulation and equals hlc3 of that bar
        // (so any nearby price would otherwise "match").
        if avwapEnabled
            float pivAvwap = avwap[barOffset]
            float pivSigma = avwapSigma[barOffset]
            if not na(pivAvwap) and not na(pivSigma) and pivSigma > 0 and math.abs(price - pivAvwap) <= td
                out := out + 'AVWAP '
            if not na(pivAvwap) and not na(pivSigma) and pivSigma > 0
                if showSigma1 and math.abs(price - (pivAvwap + sigma1Mult * pivSigma)) <= td
                    out := out + '+' + str.tostring(sigma1Mult, '#.#') + 'σ '
                if showSigma1 and math.abs(price - (pivAvwap - sigma1Mult * pivSigma)) <= td
                    out := out + '-' + str.tostring(sigma1Mult, '#.#') + 'σ '
                if showSigma2 and math.abs(price - (pivAvwap + sigma2Mult * pivSigma)) <= td
                    out := out + '+' + str.tostring(sigma2Mult, '#.#') + 'σ '
                if showSigma2 and math.abs(price - (pivAvwap - sigma2Mult * pivSigma)) <= td
                    out := out + '-' + str.tostring(sigma2Mult, '#.#') + 'σ '
                if showSigma3 and math.abs(price - (pivAvwap + sigma3Mult * pivSigma)) <= td
                    out := out + '+' + str.tostring(sigma3Mult, '#.#') + 'σ '
                if showSigma3 and math.abs(price - (pivAvwap - sigma3Mult * pivSigma)) <= td
                    out := out + '-' + str.tostring(sigma3Mult, '#.#') + 'σ '
        // Strip the trailing space left by the tag appends.
        if str.endswith(out, ' ')
            out := str.substring(out, 0, str.length(out) - 1)
        out

// Returns a string listing which tracked levels lie inside [barLow, barHigh].
// Used for iceberg confluence — we care whether the bar's whole range
// straddled a level, not just whether close was near it.
levelsInBar(float barLow, float barHigh, int barOffset) =>
    string out = ''
    if barHigh >= barLow
        // Developing-session levels — high-quality intra-session reference.
        // (Only set during the redraw block on barstate.islast, so meaningful
        // primarily in realtime; historical icebergs won't capture this.)
        if not na(currDevPOC) and currDevPOC >= barLow and currDevPOC <= barHigh
            out := out + 'POC '
        if not na(currDevVAH) and currDevVAH >= barLow and currDevVAH <= barHigh
            out := out + 'VAH '
        if not na(currDevVAL) and currDevVAL >= barLow and currDevVAL <= barHigh
            out := out + 'VAL '
        // Previous-session levels.
        if not na(prevSessPOC) and prevSessPOC >= barLow and prevSessPOC <= barHigh
            string sentSuffix = na(prevSessPOCSentiment) or prevSessPOCSentiment == 'Neutral' ? '' : '(' + prevSessPOCSentiment + ')'
            out := out + 'pPOC' + sentSuffix + ' '
        if not na(prevSessVAH) and prevSessVAH >= barLow and prevSessVAH <= barHigh
            out := out + 'pVAH '
        if not na(prevSessVAL) and prevSessVAL >= barLow and prevSessVAL <= barHigh
            out := out + 'pVAL '
        int sz = array.size(nakedPOCs)
        if sz > 0
            for i = 0 to sz - 1
                float p = array.get(nakedPOCs, i)
                if p >= barLow and p <= barHigh
                    out := out + 'nPOC@' + str.tostring(p, format.mintick) + ' '
                    break
        if avwapEnabled
            float pivAvwap = avwap[barOffset]
            float pivSigma = avwapSigma[barOffset]
            // Require pivSigma > 0 (same reasoning as checkConfluence — skips
            // session-boundary bars where AVWAP has only 1 bar of accumulation).
            if not na(pivAvwap) and not na(pivSigma) and pivSigma > 0 and pivAvwap >= barLow and pivAvwap <= barHigh
                out := out + 'AVWAP '
            if not na(pivAvwap) and not na(pivSigma) and pivSigma > 0
                float u1 = pivAvwap + sigma1Mult * pivSigma
                float l1 = pivAvwap - sigma1Mult * pivSigma
                float u2 = pivAvwap + sigma2Mult * pivSigma
                float l2 = pivAvwap - sigma2Mult * pivSigma
                float u3 = pivAvwap + sigma3Mult * pivSigma
                float l3 = pivAvwap - sigma3Mult * pivSigma
                if showSigma1 and u1 >= barLow and u1 <= barHigh
                    out := out + '+' + str.tostring(sigma1Mult, '#.#') + 'σ '
                if showSigma1 and l1 >= barLow and l1 <= barHigh
                    out := out + '-' + str.tostring(sigma1Mult, '#.#') + 'σ '
                if showSigma2 and u2 >= barLow and u2 <= barHigh
                    out := out + '+' + str.tostring(sigma2Mult, '#.#') + 'σ '
                if showSigma2 and l2 >= barLow and l2 <= barHigh
                    out := out + '-' + str.tostring(sigma2Mult, '#.#') + 'σ '
                if showSigma3 and u3 >= barLow and u3 <= barHigh
                    out := out + '+' + str.tostring(sigma3Mult, '#.#') + 'σ '
                if showSigma3 and l3 >= barLow and l3 <= barHigh
                    out := out + '-' + str.tostring(sigma3Mult, '#.#') + 'σ '
    // Strip the trailing space left by the tag appends.
    if str.endswith(out, ' ')
        out := str.substring(out, 0, str.length(out) - 1)
    out

//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// SMT DIVERGENCE
//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
drawDivergence(bool isBull, int prevBar, float prevChart, float currChart, float prevCmp, float currCmp, string sym, color col) =>
    int curBar = bar_index - pivotLen
    line.new(prevBar, prevChart, curBar, currChart, color = col, width = lineWidth, style = lineStyle)
    if showLabel
        float midPrice = (prevChart + currChart) / 2.0
        int   midBar   = math.round((prevBar + curBar) / 2.0)
        string tip = 'Chart: ' + str.tostring(prevChart, format.mintick) + ' → ' + str.tostring(currChart, format.mintick) + '\n' + shortName(sym) + ': ' + str.tostring(prevCmp, format.mintick) + ' → ' + str.tostring(currCmp, format.mintick)
        label.new(midBar, midPrice, (isBull ? 'Bull SMT\n' : 'Bear SMT\n') + shortName(sym), style = isBull ? label.style_label_up : label.style_label_down, color = col, textcolor = color.white, size = lblSize, tooltip = tip)

// ─── Bearish SMT (confirmed pivot HIGH) ─────────────────────────────────────
// Per-pivot dedup: collect every symbol that diverges, then update dashboard
// state ONCE and fire ONE combined alert. Avoids three alerts + the dashboard
// only showing whichever symbol happened to be evaluated last.
//
// Inverse-correlation sampling: at a chart pivot HIGH the chart price is
// peaking, so a TRUE inverse cmp should be at a pivot LOW. We sample the
// cmp's LOW (not HIGH) at the chart's pivot-high bar so we compare the
// "matching" cmp pivot value across consecutive chart pivots.
if not na(phVal)
    int pivotBar = bar_index - pivotLen
    float s1At = sym1Corr == 'Inverse' ? s1Low[pivotLen]  : s1High[pivotLen]
    float s2At = sym2Corr == 'Inverse' ? s2Low[pivotLen]  : s2High[pivotLen]
    float s3At = sym3Corr == 'Inverse' ? s3Low[pivotLen]  : s3High[pivotLen]

    if not na(prevPHChart)
        bool chartHH = phVal > prevPHChart
        bool chartLH = phVal < prevPHChart
        string conf = checkConfluence(phVal, confTicks, pivotLen)

        int    divCount     = 0
        string divergedSyms = ''

        if sym1Enabled and not na(s1At) and not na(prevPHS1)
            bool s1HH = s1At > prevPHS1
            bool s1LH = s1At < prevPHS1
            // Positive: divergence when directions OPPOSE.  Inverse: divergence when directions MATCH.
            bool d1 = sym1Corr == 'Positive' ? ((chartHH and s1LH) or (chartLH and s1HH)) : ((chartHH and s1HH) or (chartLH and s1LH))
            if d1
                drawDivergence(false, prevPHBar, prevPHChart, phVal, prevPHS1, s1At, sym1, bearColor)
                divergedSyms := divergedSyms + (divCount > 0 ? ', ' : '') + shortName(sym1) + (sym1Corr == 'Inverse' ? ' (inv)' : '')
                divCount     += 1

        if sym2Enabled and not na(s2At) and not na(prevPHS2)
            bool s2HH = s2At > prevPHS2
            bool s2LH = s2At < prevPHS2
            bool d2 = sym2Corr == 'Positive' ? ((chartHH and s2LH) or (chartLH and s2HH)) : ((chartHH and s2HH) or (chartLH and s2LH))
            if d2
                drawDivergence(false, prevPHBar, prevPHChart, phVal, prevPHS2, s2At, sym2, bearColor)
                divergedSyms := divergedSyms + (divCount > 0 ? ', ' : '') + shortName(sym2) + (sym2Corr == 'Inverse' ? ' (inv)' : '')
                divCount     += 1

        if sym3Enabled and not na(s3At) and not na(prevPHS3)
            bool s3HH = s3At > prevPHS3
            bool s3LH = s3At < prevPHS3
            bool d3 = sym3Corr == 'Positive' ? ((chartHH and s3LH) or (chartLH and s3HH)) : ((chartHH and s3HH) or (chartLH and s3LH))
            if d3
                drawDivergence(false, prevPHBar, prevPHChart, phVal, prevPHS3, s3At, sym3, bearColor)
                divergedSyms := divergedSyms + (divCount > 0 ? ', ' : '') + shortName(sym3) + (sym3Corr == 'Inverse' ? ' (inv)' : '')
                divCount     += 1

        if divCount > 0
            lastBearBar   := pivotBar
            lastBearSym   := divergedSyms
            lastBearPrice := phVal
            lastBearConf  := str.length(conf) > 0
            if alertBear
                string base = 'Bearish SMT vs ' + divergedSyms
                string msg  = str.length(conf) > 0 ? base + ' | Confluence: ' + conf : base
                alert(msg, alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)

    prevPHChart := phVal
    prevPHS1    := s1At
    prevPHS2    := s2At
    prevPHS3    := s3At
    prevPHBar   := pivotBar

// ─── Bullish SMT (confirmed pivot LOW) ──────────────────────────────────────
// Inverse sampling (mirror of the bearish block): at a chart pivot LOW the
// chart price is troughing, so a TRUE inverse cmp should be at a pivot HIGH.
// We sample cmp's HIGH (not LOW) at the chart's pivot-low bar.
if not na(plVal)
    int pivotBar = bar_index - pivotLen
    float s1At = sym1Corr == 'Inverse' ? s1High[pivotLen] : s1Low[pivotLen]
    float s2At = sym2Corr == 'Inverse' ? s2High[pivotLen] : s2Low[pivotLen]
    float s3At = sym3Corr == 'Inverse' ? s3High[pivotLen] : s3Low[pivotLen]

    if not na(prevPLChart)
        bool chartLL = plVal < prevPLChart
        bool chartHL = plVal > prevPLChart
        string conf = checkConfluence(plVal, confTicks, pivotLen)

        int    divCount     = 0
        string divergedSyms = ''

        if sym1Enabled and not na(s1At) and not na(prevPLS1)
            bool s1LL = s1At < prevPLS1
            bool s1HL = s1At > prevPLS1
            // Positive: divergence when directions OPPOSE.  Inverse: divergence when directions MATCH.
            bool d1 = sym1Corr == 'Positive' ? ((chartLL and s1HL) or (chartHL and s1LL)) : ((chartLL and s1LL) or (chartHL and s1HL))
            if d1
                drawDivergence(true, prevPLBar, prevPLChart, plVal, prevPLS1, s1At, sym1, bullColor)
                divergedSyms := divergedSyms + (divCount > 0 ? ', ' : '') + shortName(sym1) + (sym1Corr == 'Inverse' ? ' (inv)' : '')
                divCount     += 1

        if sym2Enabled and not na(s2At) and not na(prevPLS2)
            bool s2LL = s2At < prevPLS2
            bool s2HL = s2At > prevPLS2
            bool d2 = sym2Corr == 'Positive' ? ((chartLL and s2HL) or (chartHL and s2LL)) : ((chartLL and s2LL) or (chartHL and s2HL))
            if d2
                drawDivergence(true, prevPLBar, prevPLChart, plVal, prevPLS2, s2At, sym2, bullColor)
                divergedSyms := divergedSyms + (divCount > 0 ? ', ' : '') + shortName(sym2) + (sym2Corr == 'Inverse' ? ' (inv)' : '')
                divCount     += 1

        if sym3Enabled and not na(s3At) and not na(prevPLS3)
            bool s3LL = s3At < prevPLS3
            bool s3HL = s3At > prevPLS3
            bool d3 = sym3Corr == 'Positive' ? ((chartLL and s3HL) or (chartHL and s3LL)) : ((chartLL and s3LL) or (chartHL and s3HL))
            if d3
                drawDivergence(true, prevPLBar, prevPLChart, plVal, prevPLS3, s3At, sym3, bullColor)
                divergedSyms := divergedSyms + (divCount > 0 ? ', ' : '') + shortName(sym3) + (sym3Corr == 'Inverse' ? ' (inv)' : '')
                divCount     += 1

        if divCount > 0
            lastBullBar   := pivotBar
            lastBullSym   := divergedSyms
            lastBullPrice := plVal
            lastBullConf  := str.length(conf) > 0
            if alertBull
                string base = 'Bullish SMT vs ' + divergedSyms
                string msg  = str.length(conf) > 0 ? base + ' | Confluence: ' + conf : base
                alert(msg, alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)

    prevPLChart := plVal
    prevPLS1    := s1At
    prevPLS2    := s2At
    prevPLS3    := s3At
    prevPLBar   := pivotBar

plotshape(showPivotMarkers and not na(phVal), title = 'Pivot High', style = shape.triangledown, location = location.abovebar, color = color.new(GRAY, 0), size = size.tiny, offset = -pivotLen)
plotshape(showPivotMarkers and not na(plVal), title = 'Pivot Low',  style = shape.triangleup,   location = location.belowbar, color = color.new(GRAY, 0), size = size.tiny, offset = -pivotLen)

//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// VOLUME PROFILE — uses session boundary detection from the helpers section.
//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 1) Session finalization — compute the just-completed session's POC/VAH/VAL
//    BEFORE we reset for the new session. Save as previous-session levels and
//    push the POC to the naked-POC list.
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
if vpEnabled and isNewVPSession and not na(vpSessHigh) and vpSessHigh > vpSessLow
    // Recompute bins from the JUST-COMPLETED session's bars before computing
    // prev-session POC/VAH/VAL. offset 1 = previous bar (last bar of prior
    // session); offset bar_index - vpSessStart = first bar of prior session.
    // The current bar (offset 0) is the first bar of the NEW session and
    // must be excluded from prior-session aggregation.
    recomputeBinsFromRaw(1, bar_index - vpSessStart)
    [fPocIdx, fVaL, fVaH, fTotalV] = computeProfile(vpBins, vpRows, vpValueAreaP)
    if fTotalV > 0
        float fBinSize = (vpSessHigh - vpSessLow) / vpRows
        float fPOC = vpSessLow + (fPocIdx + 0.5) * fBinSize
        float fVAH = vpSessLow + (fVaH + 1) * fBinSize
        float fVAL = vpSessLow + fVaL * fBinSize

        // Save scalar levels.
        prevSessPOC := fPOC
        prevSessVAH := fVAH
        prevSessVAL := fVAL
        prevSessStartBar := vpSessStart
        prevSessEndBar   := bar_index - 1

        // POC bin sentiment — used to enrich confluence tags (pPOC(Bull/Bear)).
        // 60%+ bull = Bull, 40%- bull = Bear, otherwise Neutral.
        float fPocTotal = array.get(vpBins,     fPocIdx)
        float fPocBull  = array.get(vpBinsBull, fPocIdx)
        if fPocTotal > 0
            float bullRatio = fPocBull / fPocTotal
            prevSessPOCSentiment := bullRatio >= 0.6 ? 'Bull' : bullRatio <= 0.4 ? 'Bear' : 'Neutral'
        else
            prevSessPOCSentiment := 'Neutral'

        // Replace previous-session drawings.
        if not na(prevPocLine)
            line.delete(prevPocLine)
        if not na(prevVahLine)
            line.delete(prevVahLine)
        if not na(prevValLine)
            line.delete(prevValLine)
        if not na(prevPocLabel)
            label.delete(prevPocLabel)
        if not na(prevVahLabel)
            label.delete(prevVahLabel)
        if not na(prevValLabel)
            label.delete(prevValLabel)

        if vpShowPrev
            prevPocLine := line.new(prevSessStartBar, fPOC, prevSessEndBar, fPOC, color = vpPrevPocColor, width = vpPrevLineWidth, style = line.style_solid, extend = extend.right)
            prevVahLine := line.new(prevSessStartBar, fVAH, prevSessEndBar, fVAH, color = vpPrevVaColor,  width = 1, style = line.style_dotted, extend = extend.right)
            prevValLine := line.new(prevSessStartBar, fVAL, prevSessEndBar, fVAL, color = vpPrevVaColor,  width = 1, style = line.style_dotted, extend = extend.right)
            if vpShowLabels
                int prevLabelBar = bar_index + 1
                prevPocLabel := label.new(prevLabelBar, fPOC, 'pPOC ' + str.tostring(fPOC, format.mintick), style = label.style_label_left, color = vpPrevPocColor, textcolor = color.white, size = size.small)
                prevVahLabel := label.new(prevLabelBar, fVAH, 'pVAH ' + str.tostring(fVAH, format.mintick), style = label.style_label_left, color = vpPrevVaColor,  textcolor = color.white, size = size.small)
                prevValLabel := label.new(prevLabelBar, fVAL, 'pVAL ' + str.tostring(fVAL, format.mintick), style = label.style_label_left, color = vpPrevVaColor,  textcolor = color.white, size = size.small)

        // Push the finalized POC onto the naked-POC list. NOTE: we store
        // `bar_index` (the current bar = creation bar) — not `prevSessStartBar`
        // — so the 1-bar grace period in the touch check actually works.
        // Using `prevSessStartBar` here is the previously-shipped bug: the
        // grace check `bar_index > created + 1` would have been true on the
        // very first bar of the new session (since prevSessStartBar is way
        // back), letting an opening-bar straddle invalidate the nPOC instantly.
        if nPocEnabled
            line nLine = line.new(prevSessStartBar, fPOC, bar_index, fPOC, color = nPocColor, width = 1, style = nPocStyle, extend = extend.right)
            label nLabel = nPocLabels ? label.new(bar_index + 1, fPOC, 'nPOC ' + str.tostring(fPOC, format.mintick), style = label.style_label_left, color = nPocColor, textcolor = color.white, size = size.tiny) : na
            array.push(nakedPOCs,            fPOC)
            array.push(nakedPOCCreationBars, bar_index)
            array.push(nakedPOCLines,        nLine)
            array.push(nakedPOCLabels,       nLabel)

            // Prune oldest if over the max-tracked limit.
            while array.size(nakedPOCs) > nPocMax
                array.shift(nakedPOCs)
                array.shift(nakedPOCCreationBars)
                line   oldL  = array.shift(nakedPOCLines)
                label  oldLb = array.shift(nakedPOCLabels)
                line.delete(oldL)
                if not na(oldLb)
                    label.delete(oldLb)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 2) Naked POC touch check — remove any whose price was touched this bar.
//    Skip the bar of creation (grace period) so a session-end straddle doesn't
//    instantly invalidate the just-created POC.
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
if vpEnabled and nPocEnabled and barstate.isconfirmed and array.size(nakedPOCs) > 0
    int origSz = array.size(nakedPOCs)
    for n = 0 to origSz - 1
        int idx = origSz - 1 - n
        if idx < array.size(nakedPOCs)
            int created = array.get(nakedPOCCreationBars, idx)
            // 1-bar grace as documented — skip only the creation bar itself.
            // (Previously `> created + 1` was actually a 2-bar grace.)
            if bar_index > created
                float p = array.get(nakedPOCs, idx)
                if high >= p and low <= p
                    line  oldL  = array.get(nakedPOCLines, idx)
                    label oldLb = array.get(nakedPOCLabels, idx)
                    line.delete(oldL)
                    if not na(oldLb)
                        label.delete(oldLb)
                    array.remove(nakedPOCs,            idx)
                    array.remove(nakedPOCCreationBars, idx)
                    array.remove(nakedPOCLines,        idx)
                    array.remove(nakedPOCLabels,       idx)

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 3) Session reset — clears developing-profile drawings refs (orphans them as
//    historical), resets aggregates.
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
if vpEnabled and (isNewVPSession or na(vpSessHigh))
    // Histogram boxes (vol + sentiment) are orphaned — they remain visible
    // as historical profile reference, anchored at the past session's right
    // edge (they don't intrude on the new session's chart space).
    //
    // HVN/LVN lines and per-bin volume labels, however, are session-specific
    // markers that would either visually clutter subsequent sessions or
    // accumulate against Pine's 500-label budget. Explicitly DELETE these
    // on session reset rather than orphan them.
    array.clear(vpBoxes)
    array.clear(vpSentBoxes)
    if array.size(vpHVNLines) > 0
        for j = 0 to array.size(vpHVNLines) - 1
            line.delete(array.get(vpHVNLines, j))
        array.clear(vpHVNLines)
    if array.size(vpBinLabels) > 0
        for j = 0 to array.size(vpBinLabels) - 1
            label.delete(array.get(vpBinLabels, j))
        array.clear(vpBinLabels)
    vpPocLine   := na
    vpVahLine   := na
    vpValLine   := na
    vpPocLabel  := na
    vpVahLabel  := na
    vpValLabel  := na
    vpHighLabel := na
    vpLowLabel  := na
    // Reset session aggregates.
    vpSessHigh  := high
    vpSessLow   := low
    vpSessStart := bar_index
    array.fill(vpBins,     0.0)
    array.fill(vpBinsBull, 0.0)
    currDevPOC := na
    currDevVAH := na
    currDevVAL := na
    hvnCount := 0
    lvnCount := 0
    vpSessBarCount := 1
    lastRecompHigh := na
    lastRecompLow  := na
else if vpEnabled
    vpSessHigh := math.max(vpSessHigh, high)
    vpSessLow  := math.min(vpSessLow, low)
    if barstate.isconfirmed
        vpSessBarCount := vpSessBarCount + 1

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 4) Bin recomputation — drift-free, incremental when stable.
//    The previous v2.0 implementation did a full `recomputeBinsFromRaw` on
//    every confirmed bar — correct but O(N²·R) cumulatively across a session.
//    On extreme combos (Weekly+ anchor on M1 + vpRows=80) the late-session
//    recomputes exceeded Pine's per-bar loop budget.
//    The fix: only do a full recompute when the session range has actually
//    changed since the last recompute. While the range is stable, just add
//    the current bar's volume incrementally — bins are already aligned
//    correctly. Typical session: 5-10 recomputes (early), N-K incrementals.
//    Worst case (range expands every bar) degrades back to O(N²·R), same as
//    before — but typical case becomes O(N·R), matching naive incremental
//    approach in cost while remaining drift-free.
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
if vpEnabled and barstate.isconfirmed and not na(vpSessHigh) and vpSessHigh > vpSessLow
    bool rangeChanged = na(lastRecompHigh) or na(lastRecompLow) or vpSessHigh != lastRecompHigh or vpSessLow != lastRecompLow
    if rangeChanged
        recomputeBinsFromRaw(0, bar_index - vpSessStart)
        lastRecompHigh := vpSessHigh
        lastRecompLow  := vpSessLow
    else
        accumulateCurrentBar()

//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 5) Redraw developing profile on the chart's last bar.
//    Gated so we only delete-and-rebuild the histogram boxes when something
//    actually changed: (a) initial load, (b) bar advanced (new bar's first
//    execution), or (c) the bar just closed and bins were updated. On a fast
//    intraday chart this drops ~99% of redundant redraws while still keeping
//    the histogram current.
//──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
vpHasData = array.sum(vpBins) > 0
vpShouldRedraw = barstate.islast and (na(lastVpDrawBar) or bar_index != lastVpDrawBar or barstate.isconfirmed)
if vpShouldRedraw and vpEnabled and vpHasData and not na(vpSessHigh) and vpSessHigh > vpSessLow
    lastVpDrawBar := bar_index
    // ── Cleanup current developing drawings ──────────────────────────────
    if array.size(vpBoxes) > 0
        for j = 0 to array.size(vpBoxes) - 1
            box.delete(array.get(vpBoxes, j))
        array.clear(vpBoxes)
    if array.size(vpSentBoxes) > 0
        for j = 0 to array.size(vpSentBoxes) - 1
            box.delete(array.get(vpSentBoxes, j))
        array.clear(vpSentBoxes)
    if array.size(vpHVNLines) > 0
        for j = 0 to array.size(vpHVNLines) - 1
            line.delete(array.get(vpHVNLines, j))
        array.clear(vpHVNLines)
    if array.size(vpBinLabels) > 0
        for j = 0 to array.size(vpBinLabels) - 1
            label.delete(array.get(vpBinLabels, j))
        array.clear(vpBinLabels)
    if not na(vpPocLine)
        line.delete(vpPocLine)
    if not na(vpVahLine)
        line.delete(vpVahLine)
    if not na(vpValLine)
        line.delete(vpValLine)
    if not na(vpPocLabel)
        label.delete(vpPocLabel)
    if not na(vpVahLabel)
        label.delete(vpVahLabel)
    if not na(vpValLabel)
        label.delete(vpValLabel)
    if not na(vpHighLabel)
        label.delete(vpHighLabel)
    if not na(vpLowLabel)
        label.delete(vpLowLabel)

    // ── Compute profile metrics ─────────────────────────────────────────
    [dPocIdx, dVaL, dVaH, dTotalV] = computeProfile(vpBins, vpRows, vpValueAreaP)

    float maxBinVol = 0.0
    float maxAbsBBP = 0.0
    for i = 0 to vpRows - 1
        float v = array.get(vpBins, i)
        if v > maxBinVol
            maxBinVol := v
        float bbp = math.abs(2.0 * array.get(vpBinsBull, i) - v)
        if bbp > maxAbsBBP
            maxAbsBBP := bbp

    float binSize  = (vpSessHigh - vpSessLow) / vpRows
    float pocPrice = vpSessLow + (dPocIdx + 0.5) * binSize
    float vahPrice = vpSessLow + (dVaH + 1) * binSize
    float valPrice = vpSessLow + dVaL * binSize

    currDevPOC := pocPrice
    currDevVAH := vahPrice
    currDevVAL := valPrice

    // ── Layout: single histogram OR twin (sentiment + volume) ───────────
    bool   twinMode      = vpProfileLayout == 'Twin (Volume + Sentiment)'
    int    halfWidth     = math.max(2, vpHistWidth / 2 - 1)
    int    profileLeftBar  = bar_index + 1

    // In Twin mode: sentiment on the LEFT (closer to chart), volume on the
    // RIGHT (further out). In Single mode: only the volume histogram is drawn.
    int sentLeftBar  = profileLeftBar
    int sentRightCap = profileLeftBar + halfWidth
    int volLeftBar   = twinMode ? sentRightCap + 2 : profileLeftBar
    int volRightCap  = volLeftBar + (twinMode ? halfWidth : vpHistWidth)
    int profileRightCap = volRightCap   // for the right-edge labels

    int lineLeft  = vpSessStart
    int lineRight = bar_index

    // ── Reset HVN/LVN counts so the dashboard reflects current profile ─
    hvnCount := 0
    lvnCount := 0

    // ── Per-bin loop: sentiment box + volume box + HVN/LVN + bin labels ─
    if maxBinVol > 0
        for i = 0 to vpRows - 1
            float v = array.get(vpBins, i)
            if v > 0
                float vBull = array.get(vpBinsBull, i)
                float vBear = v - vBull
                float bbp   = vBull - vBear       // signed net pressure
                float LpM   = v / maxBinVol       // ratio to POC bin
                float DpM   = maxAbsBBP > 0 ? math.abs(bbp) / maxAbsBBP : 0.0

                float binLowPrice  = vpSessLow + i * binSize
                float binHighPrice = binLowPrice + binSize
                float binMidPrice  = binLowPrice + binSize * 0.5

                // ── Sentiment histogram bin (twin layout only) ──────────
                // Don't force a minimum width — let near-balanced bins be
                // visually quiet rather than rounded up to a misleading 1-bar
                // box.
                if twinMode and vpShowHist and DpM > 0
                    int sentBarW = math.round(DpM * halfWidth)
                    if sentBarW > 0
                        color sentColor = bbp > 0 ? vpTwinSentBull : bbp < 0 ? vpTwinSentBear : vpNeutralBinColor
                        box sb = box.new(sentLeftBar, binHighPrice, sentLeftBar + sentBarW, binLowPrice, border_color = na, bgcolor = sentColor)
                        array.push(vpSentBoxes, sb)

                // ── Volume histogram bin ────────────────────────────────
                int volBarW = math.round(LpM * (twinMode ? halfWidth : vpHistWidth))
                if vpShowHist and volBarW > 0
                    color volColor = vpOutFill
                    if twinMode
                        volColor := vpTwinVolColor    // neutral — sentiment is shown separately
                    else if vpSentiment
                        volColor := bbp > 0 ? vpBullBinColor : bbp < 0 ? vpBearBinColor : vpNeutralBinColor
                    else
                        bool inVA = i >= dVaL and i <= dVaH
                        volColor := inVA ? vpVaFill : vpOutFill
                    box vb = box.new(volLeftBar, binHighPrice, volLeftBar + volBarW, binLowPrice, border_color = na, bgcolor = volColor)
                    array.push(vpBoxes, vb)

                    // ── Per-bin volume label (optional) ─────────────────
                    if vpShowBinLabels
                        float pctOfSess = dTotalV > 0 ? v / dTotalV * 100.0 : 0.0
                        string binText = str.tostring(v, format.volume) + ' (' + str.tostring(pctOfSess, '#.##') + '%)'
                        label bl = label.new(volLeftBar + volBarW, binMidPrice, binText, style = label.style_none, textcolor = chart.fg_color, size = size.tiny, textalign = text.align_left)
                        array.push(vpBinLabels, bl)

                // ── HVN / LVN markers (skip the POC bin) ────────────────
                // Always extend.none — these are session-bound markers, not
                // forward-reference levels. Extending them right (alongside
                // POC/VAH/VAL) would clutter subsequent sessions.
                if vpShowHVN and i != dPocIdx
                    if LpM >= vpHVNThreshold
                        hvnCount += 1
                        line hl = line.new(lineLeft, binMidPrice, lineRight, binMidPrice, color = vpHVNColor, width = 1, style = line.style_solid, extend = extend.none)
                        array.push(vpHVNLines, hl)
                    else if LpM <= vpLVNThreshold
                        lvnCount += 1
                        line ll = line.new(lineLeft, binMidPrice, lineRight, binMidPrice, color = vpLVNColor, width = 1, style = line.style_dotted, extend = extend.none)
                        array.push(vpHVNLines, ll)

    // ── POC / VAH / VAL across-session lines ─────────────────────────────
    if vpShowPOC
        vpPocLine := line.new(lineLeft, pocPrice, lineRight, pocPrice, color = vpPocColor, width = 2, extend = vpExtend ? extend.right : extend.none)
    if vpShowVA
        vpVahLine := line.new(lineLeft, vahPrice, lineRight, vahPrice, color = vpVaColor, width = 1, style = line.style_dashed, extend = vpExtend ? extend.right : extend.none)
        vpValLine := line.new(lineLeft, valPrice, lineRight, valPrice, color = vpVaColor, width = 1, style = line.style_dashed, extend = vpExtend ? extend.right : extend.none)

    // ── Right-edge POC/VAH/VAL price labels ──────────────────────────────
    if vpShowLabels
        int priceLabelBar = profileRightCap + 2
        if vpShowPOC
            vpPocLabel := label.new(priceLabelBar, pocPrice, 'POC ' + str.tostring(pocPrice, format.mintick), style = label.style_label_left, color = vpPocColor, textcolor = color.white, size = size.small)
        if vpShowVA
            vpVahLabel := label.new(priceLabelBar, vahPrice, 'VAH ' + str.tostring(vahPrice, format.mintick), style = label.style_label_left, color = vpVaColor, textcolor = color.white, size = size.small)
            vpValLabel := label.new(priceLabelBar, valPrice, 'VAL ' + str.tostring(valPrice, format.mintick), style = label.style_label_left, color = vpVaColor, textcolor = color.white, size = size.small)

    // ── Profile-edge labels: Profile High / Profile Low ─────────────────
    if vpShowEdgeLabels and vpSessHigh > 0
        float rangePct = (vpSessHigh - vpSessLow) / vpSessLow * 100.0
        string totalLabel = vpSource == 'Money Flow' ? 'Total Money Flow: ' : 'Total Volume: '
        string highTip = 'Profile High — ' + str.tostring(vpSessHigh, format.mintick) + '\n' + str.tostring(rangePct, '#.##') + '% above Profile Low\n' + totalLabel + str.tostring(dTotalV, format.volume) + '\nBars: ' + str.tostring(vpSessBarCount)
        string lowTip  = 'Profile Low — '  + str.tostring(vpSessLow,  format.mintick) + '\n' + str.tostring(rangePct, '#.##') + '% below Profile High\n' + totalLabel + str.tostring(dTotalV, format.volume) + '\nBars: ' + str.tostring(vpSessBarCount)
        vpHighLabel := label.new(lineRight, vpSessHigh, str.tostring(vpSessHigh, format.mintick), style = label.style_label_down, color = color.new(vpPocColor, 30), textcolor = color.white, size = size.small, tooltip = highTip)
        vpLowLabel  := label.new(lineRight, vpSessLow,  str.tostring(vpSessLow,  format.mintick), style = label.style_label_up,   color = color.new(vpPocColor, 30), textcolor = color.white, size = size.small, tooltip = lowTip)

//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// ICEBERG / ABSORPTION DETECTION
//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// True iceberg orders need order-book data Pine cannot access. This is the
// standard proxy: a bar with abnormally high volume but a narrow range,
// closing at one extreme, has effectively "absorbed" supply or demand at a
// single price — the footprint a resting iceberg leaves on a candlestick.

// Top-level (non-conditional) so warmup is correct. We use the [1]-offset
// trailing values — i.e., SMA and ATR computed through the PREVIOUS bar — so
// the current bar's own volume/range doesn't dilute the threshold it's being
// compared against. (A 2× volume spike was previously raising its own SMA,
// causing the actual ratio to fall just under iceVolMult.)
volSMA = ta.sma(volume, 20)[1]
atr14  = ta.atr(14)[1]

// Reset session counter on the same anchor as VP.
if isNewVPSession
    iceCount := 0

if iceEnabled and barstate.isconfirmed and not na(volSMA) and volSMA > 0 and not na(atr14) and atr14 > 0
    float barRange = high - low
    if barRange > 0
        bool volSpike   = volume > iceVolMult * volSMA
        bool narrowRange = barRange < iceRangeMult * atr14
        bool closeHigh  = close >= high - iceCloseThreshold * barRange
        bool closeLow   = close <= low  + iceCloseThreshold * barRange

        // Mutually exclusive — at iceCloseThreshold = 0.5 a doji bar (close
        // exactly at midpoint) would satisfy BOTH closeHigh AND closeLow.
        // Skip both rather than arbitrarily picking Bull, since a midpoint
        // close is genuinely ambiguous (neither side absorbed).
        bool isBullIce = volSpike and narrowRange and closeHigh and not closeLow
        bool isBearIce = volSpike and narrowRange and closeLow  and not closeHigh

        if isBullIce or isBearIce
            string confluence = levelsInBar(low, high, 0)
            bool hasConf = str.length(confluence) > 0
            if not iceRequireConf or hasConf
                bool   isBull = isBullIce
                color  c      = isBull ? iceBullColor : iceBearColor
                float  yPos   = isBull ? low : high
                string typeS  = isBull ? 'Bull' : 'Bear'
                string txt    = iceMarkerText + (hasConf ? ' ★' : '')
                string tip    = 'Iceberg ' + typeS + ' Absorption\n' + 'Volume: ' + str.tostring(volume / volSMA, '#.#') + 'x avg\n' + 'Range: ' + str.tostring(barRange / atr14, '#.##') + ' ATR\n' + 'Close: ' + str.tostring((close - low) / barRange * 100, '#') + '% of bar' + (hasConf ? '\nLevels: ' + confluence : '')
                label.new(bar_index, yPos, txt, style = isBull ? label.style_label_up : label.style_label_down, color = c, textcolor = color.white, size = getLabelSize(iceMarkerSize), tooltip = tip)

                iceCount    := iceCount + 1
                lastIceBar  := bar_index
                lastIceType := typeS
                lastIceConf := hasConf

                if iceAlertEnabled
                    alert(typeS + 'ish Iceberg' + (hasConf ? ' | ' + confluence : ''), alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)

//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// DASHBOARD
//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
if showDash and barstate.islast
    if na(dashTable)
        dashTable := table.new(getDashPosition(dashPos), 2, 20, bgcolor = color.new(color.black, 70), border_width = 1, border_color = color.new(color.gray, 60), frame_width = 1, frame_color = color.new(color.gray, 40))

    color hdrBg = color.new(color.gray, 50)
    color rowBg = color.new(color.black, 50)
    color lblTx = color.new(color.white, 0)

    // Header.
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 0, 'SMT+VP+Ice', text_color = color.white, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = hdrBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 0, 'v2.1',       text_color = color.new(color.white, 40), text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = hdrBg)

    // Current developing levels.
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 1, 'Curr POC', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 1, na(currDevPOC) ? '—' : str.tostring(currDevPOC, format.mintick), text_color = vpPocColor, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 2, 'Curr VAH', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 2, na(currDevVAH) ? '—' : str.tostring(currDevVAH, format.mintick), text_color = vpVaColor, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 3, 'Curr VAL', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 3, na(currDevVAL) ? '—' : str.tostring(currDevVAL, format.mintick), text_color = vpVaColor, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)

    // Previous session.
    string prevPocCell = na(prevSessPOC) ? '—' : str.tostring(prevSessPOC, format.mintick) + (na(prevSessPOCSentiment) or prevSessPOCSentiment == 'Neutral' ? '' : ' (' + prevSessPOCSentiment + ')')
    color  prevPocCol  = na(prevSessPOC) ? color.gray : (prevSessPOCSentiment == 'Bull' ? GREEN : prevSessPOCSentiment == 'Bear' ? RED : vpPrevPocColor)
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 4, 'Prev POC', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 4, prevPocCell, text_color = prevPocCol, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 5, 'Prev VAH', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 5, na(prevSessVAH) ? '—' : str.tostring(prevSessVAH, format.mintick), text_color = vpPrevVaColor,  text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 6, 'Prev VAL', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 6, na(prevSessVAL) ? '—' : str.tostring(prevSessVAL, format.mintick), text_color = vpPrevVaColor,  text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)

    // Price vs prior Value Area.
    string vaPosTxt = '—'
    color  vaPosCol = color.gray
    if not na(prevSessVAH) and not na(prevSessVAL)
        if close > prevSessVAH
            vaPosTxt := 'Above'
            vaPosCol := GREEN
        else if close < prevSessVAL
            vaPosTxt := 'Below'
            vaPosCol := RED
        else
            vaPosTxt := 'Inside'
            vaPosCol := GOLD
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 7, 'Price vs pVA', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 7, vaPosTxt, text_color = vaPosCol, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)

    // AVWAP and σ levels (current bar — uses live projection).
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 8, 'AVWAP', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 8, na(avwap) ? '—' : str.tostring(avwap, format.mintick), text_color = avwapColor, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 9, '±' + str.tostring(sigma1Mult, '#.#') + 'σ', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 9, na(avwapU1) ? '—' : str.tostring(avwapL1, format.mintick) + ' / ' + str.tostring(avwapU1, format.mintick), text_color = sigma1Color, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 10, '±' + str.tostring(sigma2Mult, '#.#') + 'σ', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 10, na(avwapU2) ? '—' : str.tostring(avwapL2, format.mintick) + ' / ' + str.tostring(avwapU2, format.mintick), text_color = sigma2Color, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)

    // Naked POC count.
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 11, 'Naked POCs', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 11, str.tostring(array.size(nakedPOCs)), text_color = nPocColor, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)

    // Last SMT events.
    string bullTxt = na(lastBullBar) ? '—' : lastBullSym + ' (' + str.tostring(bar_index - lastBullBar) + ' bars ago)' + (lastBullConf ? ' ★' : '')
    string bearTxt = na(lastBearBar) ? '—' : lastBearSym + ' (' + str.tostring(bar_index - lastBearBar) + ' bars ago)' + (lastBearConf ? ' ★' : '')
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 12, 'Last Bull SMT', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 12, bullTxt, text_color = bullColor, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 13, 'Last Bear SMT', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 13, bearTxt, text_color = bearColor, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)

    // Iceberg / absorption stats.
    string iceTxt = na(lastIceBar) ? '—' : lastIceType + ' (' + str.tostring(bar_index - lastIceBar) + ' bars ago)' + (lastIceConf ? ' ★' : '')
    color  iceCol = na(lastIceBar) ? color.gray : (lastIceType == 'Bull' ? iceBullColor : iceBearColor)
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 14, 'Icebergs (sess)', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 14, str.tostring(iceCount), text_color = iceCount > 0 ? color.white : color.gray, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 15, 'Last Iceberg', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 15, iceTxt, text_color = iceCol, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)

    // Session sentiment summary (developing-session bull/bear split).
    float sessTotal = array.sum(vpBins)
    float sessBull  = array.sum(vpBinsBull)
    float bullPct   = sessTotal > 0 ? sessBull / sessTotal * 100 : na
    string sentTxt  = na(bullPct) ? '—' : str.tostring(bullPct, '#') + '% Bull / ' + str.tostring(100 - bullPct, '#') + '% Bear'
    color  sentCol  = na(bullPct) ? color.gray : (bullPct >= 55 ? GREEN : bullPct <= 45 ? RED : GOLD)
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 16, 'Sentiment', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 16, sentTxt, text_color = sentCol, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)

    // HVN / LVN counts (developing-session). Shows '—' if HVN tracking is off.
    string hvnTxt = vpShowHVN ? str.tostring(hvnCount) + ' / ' + str.tostring(lvnCount) : '—'
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 17, 'HVN / LVN', text_color = lblTx, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 17, hvnTxt, text_color = vpShowHVN ? color.white : color.gray, text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)

    // Footer hint.
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 18, 'Session',  text_color = color.new(color.white, 40), text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 18, vpAnchorIn, text_color = color.new(color.white, 40), text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 0, 19, '★ = confluence', text_color = color.new(color.white, 50), text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)
    table.cell(dashTable, 1, 19, '', text_color = color.new(color.white, 50), text_size = dashTxtSz, bgcolor = rowBg)

//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// ANCHORED VWAP — PLOTS
//══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Break the line at session boundaries by plotting na on the first bar of
// a new session. The AVWAP value itself is correctly reset above, but Pine's
// plot() would otherwise connect last-bar-of-prev-session to first-bar-of-new.
plotAvwap = avwapEnabled and not isNewVPSession ? avwap   : na
plotU1    = avwapEnabled and showSigma1 and not isNewVPSession ? avwapU1 : na
plotL1    = avwapEnabled and showSigma1 and not isNewVPSession ? avwapL1 : na
plotU2    = avwapEnabled and showSigma2 and not isNewVPSession ? avwapU2 : na
plotL2    = avwapEnabled and showSigma2 and not isNewVPSession ? avwapL2 : na
plotU3    = avwapEnabled and showSigma3 and not isNewVPSession ? avwapU3 : na
plotL3    = avwapEnabled and showSigma3 and not isNewVPSession ? avwapL3 : na

avwapPlot = plot(plotAvwap, 'AVWAP',    color = avwapColor,  linewidth = avwapWidth)
u1Plot    = plot(plotU1,    'AVWAP +1σ', color = sigma1Color, linewidth = 1)
l1Plot    = plot(plotL1,    'AVWAP -1σ', color = sigma1Color, linewidth = 1)
u2Plot    = plot(plotU2,    'AVWAP +2σ', color = sigma2Color, linewidth = 1)
l2Plot    = plot(plotL2,    'AVWAP -2σ', color = sigma2Color, linewidth = 1)
u3Plot    = plot(plotU3,    'AVWAP +3σ', color = sigma3Color, linewidth = 1)
l3Plot    = plot(plotL3,    'AVWAP -3σ', color = sigma3Color, linewidth = 1)

fill(u1Plot, l1Plot, color = fillBands and showSigma1 ? color.new(sigma1Color, fillOpacity) : na, title = '1σ Fill')
fill(u2Plot, u1Plot, color = fillBands and showSigma2 and showSigma1 ? color.new(sigma2Color, fillOpacity) : na, title = 'Upper 1σ→2σ Fill')
fill(l1Plot, l2Plot, color = fillBands and showSigma2 and showSigma1 ? color.new(sigma2Color, fillOpacity) : na, title = 'Lower 1σ→2σ Fill')
fill(u3Plot, u2Plot, color = fillBands and showSigma3 and showSigma2 ? color.new(sigma3Color, fillOpacity) : na, title = 'Upper 2σ→3σ Fill')
fill(l2Plot, l3Plot, color = fillBands and showSigma3 and showSigma2 ? color.new(sigma3Color, fillOpacity) : na, title = 'Lower 2σ→3σ Fill')
